d the Hooker-line Stiles branch to one of the most prominent New England founding families."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Seven baptisms, then died at thirty-seven","body":"Elizabeth bore seven children between 1778 and 1791, all baptized at St. John's Church in North Haven. She died in 1792 at age thirty-seven, less than a year after the seventh baptism. Her husband Timothy Eaton remarried twice — his second wife Catherine Walter died in 1797 after producing one child, and a presumed unnamed third wife produced a son baptized in 1800; the family network shows the high cost of post-Revolutionary childbearing in colonial Connecticut."}],"slug":"elizabeth-eaton-1755"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"H00449","slug":"elizabeth-eaton-1755","n":"Elizabeth Stiles Eaton","by":1755,"dy":1792,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"I00505","slug":"timothy-eaton-1749","n":"Timothy Eaton","by":1749,"dy":1808,"sx":"u","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":1776,"children":[{"id":"H01165","slug":"hannah-eaton-1778","n":"Hannah Eaton","by":1778,"dy":1851,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01166","slug":"betsey-eaton-1780","n":"Betsey Eaton","by":1780,"dy":1850,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01167","slug":"ebenezer-eaton-1782","n":"Ebenezer Eaton","by":1782,"dy":null,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01168","slug":"mabel-eaton-1784","n":"Mabel Eaton","by":1784,"dy":null,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01169","slug":"abigail-eaton-1786","n":"Abigail Eaton","by":1786,"dy":null,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01170","slug":"louisa-eaton-1789","n":"Louisa Eaton","by":1789,"dy":1884,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"H01171","slug":"solomon-eaton-1791","n":"Solomon Eaton","by":1791,"dy":null,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"X02794","slug":"timothy-eaton-jr-1800",